How did the bar served him and friends alcohol without making sure if the id is genuine or not. If its an exclusive high end bar, they should have tech to identify a bogus id or did they get paid to overlook this basic but crucial step. In the US, even gas stations have machines to identify a bogus id because underage teens come to buy cigarettes all the time with fake ids. If these kids are caught producing bogus ids, the police will be informed and the kids will get cited, forget about Bars and clubs, they are more strict. The legal drinking age in the US is 21 years in most states. This kid would be kept in juvenile center and then once he crosses 18 years of age, he will be tried as an adult and will spend most of his life behind jail. As for the bar, they may lose their license for serving alcohol to underage kids. People blame judicial system in India but there are laws for most of the things, the challenge is to make people follow those laws.
